  "notes": "CGSTL's wideband (Kuanfu) series within the Jilin-1 program. Seeded for the Orbits surface on Florian's instruction (2026-07-05); fields await sourced fill by the weekly maintenance run. Weekly maintenance (2026-07-13), conflict flagged for Florian: a fresh Wikipedia fetch states the Kuanfu series as 'four operational satellites across two generations' (three first-gen, one second-gen, most recent launch 2023-08-25), but that figure predates this file's own already-sourced event for a six-satellite Jilin-1 Kuanfu-02B cluster launched 2024-09-20 (Gunter's Space Page, canonical), and this profile's independently computed sats_active_verified (CelesTrak) already stands at 10, above Wikipedia's claimed total of 4. Wikipedia's Kuanfu prose paragraph is evidently stale relative to the 2024-09-20 cluster launch already on file. sats_launched_total left null rather than write an unreliable figure; also checked eoPortal's Jilin/Gaofen Constellation page, which gives no Kuanfu resolution/swath/revisit/spectral-band figures (only notes Kuanfu-02A as 'the first next-generation satellite' with no performance parameters), so no EO spec fields could be filled from that source either.",
